Arjun Kapoor -LRB- -LSB- ɐrˈɟun kəˈpuːr -RSB- ; born 26 June 1985 -RRB- is an Indian actor who appears in Bollywood films .
He is the son of film producers Boney Kapoor and Mona Shourie Kapoor .
After working as an assistant director and associate producer on several films , including Kal Ho Naa Ho -LRB- 2003 -RRB- and Wanted -LRB- 2009 -RRB- , he made his acting debut with Habib Faisal 's romantic drama Ishaqzaade -LRB- 2012 -RRB- , for which he was nominated for the Filmfare Award for Best Male Debut .
Kapoor went on to portray a coal bandit in the action film Gunday -LRB- 2014 -RRB- , an aspiring writer in the romance 2 States -LRB- 2014 -RRB- and a stay-at-home husband in the romantic comedy Ki & Ka -LRB- 2016 -RRB- ; all three films earned over worldwide .
In addition to acting in film , Kapoor has hosted the 16th IIFA Awards ceremony in 2015 and the seventh season of the television reality show Fear Factor : Khatron Ke Khiladi in 2016 .